&lt;p&gt;BlueLabs is a leading provider of analytics services and technology dedicated to helping our partners do the most good with their data. Our team of analysts, scientists, engineers, and strategists hail from diverse backgrounds yet share a passion for using data to solve the world’s greatest social and analytical challenges. Since our inception we’ve worked with more than 400 organizations ranging from advocacy groups, unions, political campaigns, and international groups. In addition, we service an ever-expanding portfolio of commercial clients in the automotive, travel, CPG, entertainment, healthcare, media, and telecom industries. Along the way, we’ve developed some of the most innovative tools available in analytics, media optimization, reporting, and influencer outreach.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About The Team:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Data team serves as our in-house technical experts, supporting both internal teams and clients, across numerous programs and projects. They provide guidance on data acquisition, pipelines, and integration while maintaining a mastery of our internal voter and consumer datasets. This team also creates and maintains business intelligence reports, transforming raw data into engaging and interactive dashboards across client engagements. They are the relied upon experts for internal teams on all things reporting and provide guidance on reporting best practices, report troubleshooting, and general training on report development.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About The Role&lt;/strong&gt;:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Reporting Fellow will be provided a chance to work directly with data scientists, strategists, analysts, and client leads on meaningful, hands-on work, while being guided and supported by their manager, a Senior Reporting Analytics Manager.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Reporting Fellow will learn the ins and outs of the progressive analytics consulting space. They will gain exposure to all parts of our analytics process - from collecting and organizing data to using data to analyze trends and patterns that could become useful insights for our clients. Fellows will engage with work that focuses on some of our most important clients, all while building professional analytics experience and developing a wide range of technical skills that will be immensely valuable. Fellows will receive strong mentorship by working closely with our staff who have a broad range of knowledge in the analytics space.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Reporting Fellow will work with BlueLabs for 12 weeks this summer, with the option to be either full-time or part-time based on availability.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;In this position you will:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collect, clean, and upload datasets for use in analysis&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Write simple ad-hoc SQL queries to assist with broader analysis&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Conduct data uploads for surveys in the field for QC review&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Design dashboards in Tableau and other BI solutions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work with cross functional stakeholders, both internal and external to gather requirements for dashboards, and work iteratively with those stakeholders to ensure BI solutions met their needs&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support in the building of data pipelines used in reporting using SQL&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Create documentation for BI dashboards and pipelines detailing data sources, KPI calculations, and dashboard elements and functions&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What We Are Seeking:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience developing business intelligence dashboards using Tableau.&amp;nbsp; This experience should include requirements gathering, design, and final dashboard implementation&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience using SQL to analyze data and create datasets to be used in dashboard development

